                    <span>The Junction Boys is the story of Coach Paul Brayant, and his first years at Texas A&M, and the ten hard days at Camp Junction that he put his new team through. The coach drove most of the players to quick doing camp, less than half that made the trip to Junction remained. I read the book to learn more about Coach Brayant, the only thing I really knew about him was that at one time he had the most wins of any college football coach. My thing is that I don't really like autobiographies written in the novel form, so I'll have to read another book on the coach to learn more about him, I think I would like the movie version of this book better, but it was ok.</span>
                  
